 century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Gibbs was born in 1428, in Somerset, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Elizabeth Fenworth Lady."},"et":{"1428–":"1428–Surnud","1430–1470":"1430–1470","1450–1483":"1450–1483","1428–Male":"1428–Surnud","1430":"1430","1450":"1450","1483":"1483","1470":"1470","1428":"1428","Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1428–":"1428–Kuollut","1430–1470":"1430–1470","1450–1483":"1450–1483","1428–Male":"1428–Kuollut","1430":"1430","1450":"1450","1483":"1483","1470":"1470","1428":"1428","Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1428–":"1428–Décédé","1430–1470":"1430–1470","1450–1483":"1450–1483","1428–Male":"1428–Décédé","1430":"1430","1450":"1450","1483":"1483","1470":"1470","1428":"1428","Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Robert Gibbs est né en 1428, à Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Elizabeth Fenworth Lady."},"de":{"1428–":"1428–Verstorben","1430–1470":"1430–1470","1450–1483":"1450–1483","1428–Male":"1428–Verstorben","1430":"1430","1450":"1450","1483":"1483","1470":"1470","1428":"1428","Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Somerset, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Robert Gibbs wurde 1428 in Somerset, England, United Kingdom geboren. Er hatte mit Elizabeth Fenworth Lady mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"1428–":"1428–Desede","1430–1470":"1430–1470","1450–1483":"1450–1483","1428–Male":"1428–Desede","1430":"